 Summary and Responsibilities 
 
 In this position, you will perform operational, financial, and compliance audit projects and provide internal control consulting services to organizational management and staff. You will play a significant role in ensuring the annual internal audit plan is completed on time and under budget, with emphasis on a risk-based approach. Assist management in the attainment of their objectives and always ensure organizational and professional ethical standards of all internal audit activities are carried out in compliance with The International Standards for the Professional Practice of Internal Auditing (IIA) and audit work plan. 
 Design and perform integrated audits that cover the operational, financial, and information technology processes and systems, including the development of audit plans, audit programs, remediation recommendations, and reporting results. 
 Lead and develop four full-time staff auditors and provide assistance to external auditors as needed to enhance the overall audit process. 
 Collaborate with the Internal Audit Team members in timely completion of governance or risk management assessments and reporting on to global stakeholders. 
 Responsible for development of Internal Auditor (I & II), Senior Auditor technical knowledge on the audits and overall professional development including periodic performance evaluations of the staff assigned. 
 Planning and performing audits with minimal supervision and recognize and analyze control weaknesses, propose improvements, and effectively articulate those to process owners and business management. 
 Reviews audit scope, crafts audit objectives, and develops audit programs that examine high-risk areas impacting Company financial and operational business processes and systems.
 Evaluates design and operating effectiveness of internal controls, as well as assessing the adequacy of documentation and sufficiency of business records. 
 Advises on control deficiency remediation and assists business units with implementation of process and control improvements. 
 Fraud assessments and investigations, special projects, and other duties as assigned. 
 
 Qualifications 
 
 Minimum 4 years of internal audit/public accounting experience required.
 Minimum 2 years in leading a team. 
 Must have strong analytical skills and be proficient in spreadsheet/data processing software applications.
 Certified Public Accountant or Certified Internal Auditor-required, Certified Fraud Examiner certification is a plus. Other Certifications like CISA - is preferred and considered a plus. 
 Excellent interpersonal and communication skills (written & verbal) to interact with all levels of management. Knowledge of Spanish or French language is a plus. 
 Writes clearly and effectively to present factual information including relevant numerical data. 
 Experience with documenting business processes through narratives and flowcharts, evaluating internal controls, and identifying risks. 
 Experience with data analysis software, such as ACL, is a plus.
 Knowledge of COSO Framework and Governance and Risk Management.
 Strong organizational skills and prioritization abilities. 
 Listens attentively and obtains clarification when needed. 
 Demonstrates accuracy and thoroughness in completing assignments. 
 Meets challenges with adaptability and resourcefulness. 
 Observes safety and security procedures. 
 Ability to travel 30%+ domestic and international. 
 
